# Instructions:
#
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in your actual values in .env
# 3. For production deployment on Render, set these variables in the Render dashboard
#
# MONGO_URL:
# - Get this from MongoDB Atlas (recommended for production)
# - Format: mongodb+srv://user:pass@cluster.mongodb.net/dbname
# - Whitelist Render's IP addresses in MongoDB Atlas Network Access
#
# JWT_SECRET:
# - Generate a secure random string: openssl rand -base64 32
# - Must be at least 32 characters long
# - Keep this secret and never share it
#
# MAX_FILE_SIZE:
# - File upload limit in bytes (100MB = 104857600)
# - Adjust based on your needs
#
# CLIENT_URL:
# - Frontend URL for CORS (use your Render frontend URL in production)
# - Example: https://your-frontend.onrender.com
#
# NODE_ENV:
# - Set to 'production' on Render
# - Affects error messages and logging level
#
# PORT:
# - Render sets this automatically, no need to configure
# - Local development default: 5000